• PAST RESULTS THE NORTHERN TRUST

    Ending: 8/26/2018 Purse: $9,000,000 PAR: 71 Total FedExCup Points: 11,956 Cut: 80 professionals at E to 142 Course: Ridgewood CC
    • Thursday : Partly cloudy with light rain early in the morning. High of 80. Wind NW 10-15 mph. Friday : Sunny, with a high of 83. Wind SW 4-8 mph. Saturday : Mostly sunny. High of 82. Wind S 4-8 mph. Sunday : Partly cloudy. High of 84. Wind SW 10-15 mph.
    • Highlighted by a third-round 63 which included nine birdies, Bryson DeChambeau converted a four-shot lead into a four-stroke victory at THE NORTHERN TRUST, the first event in the FedExCup Playoffs. DeChambeau earned his third career PGA TOUR victory, and second of the season, in his 69th start at the age of 24 years, 11 months, 10 days. The 2017-18 season marked DeChambeau's first multiple-win season on TOUR. Bryson DeChambeau earned 2, 000 FedExCup points and moved to No. 1 in the FedExCup standings for the first time in his career. He replaced Dustin Johnson who finished T11 in the event. Bryson DeChambeau's four-stroke win was the second largest margin of victory at THE NORTHERN TRUST in the FedExCup era, with Jason Day's six-shot victory in 2015 the benchmark. Tony Finau finished in second place, his third runner-up in 116 PGA TOUR starts. Finau led the field in Strokes Gained:Tee-to-Green(+3.141)and Strokes Gained:Around-the-Green(+7.800). Six players played their way into the Dell Technologies Championships: Nick Watney, Bronson Burgoon, Jhonattan Vegas, Scott Stallings, Brian Stuard and Danny Lee. Six players fell out of the top 100 in the FedExCup standings and were eliminated from the Playoffs: Trey Mullinax, Brandon Harkins, Patrick Rodgers, Charl Schwartzel, Alex Cejka and Rory Sabbatini. For the first time in his career, Keegan Bradley hit all 18 greens in regulation en route to a third-round 62, tying the Ridgewood Country Club course record. He went on to finish T34 after a final-round 78. After making the cut on the number, Tiger Woods posted his first bogey-free round on the PGA TOUR since 2015, with a 68 in the third round. He went on to finish T40.
